│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By relaxing the assertion to accept cases where either chosen VF would not    │
│ generate vector instructions, we prevent false-positive assertion failures    │
│ stemming from differences between the VPlan's vector-generation gating and    │
│ the legacy model's cost-only decision. This maintains the integrity of the    │
│ check for genuine cost model disagreements while avoiding crashes on loops    │
│ like the reproducer that have control-heavy patterns not suitable for         │
│ vectorization.                                                                │
