  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is due to an assertion
firing in LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF, which checks that the
VPlan-based cost model selects the same VF as the legacy cost model, unless
certain exceptions apply (early-exit loops or additional simplifications detected
in the VPlan). For the provided loop, the VPlan-based model and the legacy model
disagree, and none of the current exception conditions are satisfied, causing the
abort.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nScalarEvolution shows the loop has an
unpredictable trip count, with a predicated backedge-taken count of %n, and flags
indicating no-wrap additions. The loop structure uses an i32 induction variable
widened to i64 for an equality exit condition, and computes a reduction-like
value using select and or. During computeBestVF, the VPlan model filters out VFs
that would not generate any vector instructions via willGenerateVectors, and
computes cost(*P, VF) for others. The legacy model uses CM.expectedCost(VF)
without the same VPlan-specific considerations and may pick a different VF. The
assertion allows disagreement when: (a) early-exit loop VPlan structure implies
legacy model is inadequate, or (b) VPlan contains additional simplifications not
accounted for by legacy model. In the reproducer, neither condition triggers, but
the models still disagree.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe immediate cause is
that the VPlan-based selection excludes VFs that would not actually produce
vector instructions, whereas the legacy model may still consider and pick such
VFs based on its cost estimation. This can result in BestFactor.Width (from
VPlan) being scalar, while LegacyVF.Width (from legacy) is vector, triggering the
assertion. The reproducer loop is heavy on control logic (icmp/select/or) and
lacks memory/vector-friendly ops, so willGenerateVectors likely returns false for
all non-scalar VFs in the VPlan path, while the legacy path does not consistently
gate its choice by willGenerateVectors in the same manner across all cases,
leading to disagreement. The assertion intends to catch real cost model
mismatches but should tolerate disagreements when vector generation isn't
possible for one of the contenders, similar to how the VPlan path already filters
them.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nModify the assertion in computeBestVF to
also tolerate disagreements when either the VPlan or legacy-selected VF would not
actually generate vector instructions, aligning the assertion's exception
conditions with the VPlan gating:\n\nEdit file
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp lines 7579-7584:\n- Current:\n
